cs.GT, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.SI 

This paper belongs to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category as it proposes a reliability extension of cooperative games and studies prominent solution concepts in such games. Additionally, the use of approximation algorithms and computational complexity analysis suggests that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The study of the core in games with few agent types may also place it in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. Finally, the focus on stability and fairness in the allocation of profit may suggest that it belongs to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
